Python Library and Sample Code for Confident CAPTCHA
version 20100621_PYTHON

Thank you for downloading this library and sample code.  The included files
are:
 * README.TXT - This document
 * captchalib.py - The Python library
 * captchalib_config.py - Configuration template
 * sample.py - The Python sample

REQUIREMENTS
 * Python 2.4, 2.5, or 2.6 is required.
 * The page that renders the Confident CAPTCHA requires jQuery 1.4.2.

USAGE

 1. Sign up for Confident CAPTCHA at:

http://confidenttechnologies.com/purchase/CAPTCHA_signup.php

 2. Create an account at:

https://login.confidenttechnologies.com

 3. Modify captchalib_config.py, filling in the API credentials from:

https://login.confidenttechnologies.com/dashboard/sites/

 4. Run the sample code:

python sample.py

This will start the sample server on http://127.0.0.1:8001, and open a browser
window to that address.

 5. Integrate the library into your code.  You need captchalib.py and a
(customized) captchalib_config.py in your project.  Look at sample.py for 
integration ideas.  Be sure to include jQuery in your page.

Please send your questions and feedback to:

https://login.confidenttechnologies.com/dashboard/contactus/general/

VERSION HISTORY

20100610_PYTHON - June 10th, 2010
 * Original release

20100621_PYTHON - June 21st, 2010
 * Updated to work with API version 20100610
 * Support the new namespaced HTML and JavaScript elements
